<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,438,905,932]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">Brachygluta abdominalis</emphasis>
(Aubé, 1833)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="121" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[140,1108,976,1144]" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aube" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[140,410,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[140,410,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">Brachygluta abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported in 
<collectingRegion box="[607,790,976,1003]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[851,990,976,1003]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka and Ogden" firstAuthor="Majka" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" pagination="761 - 764" refId="ref17421" refString="Majka CG, Ogden J (2006) Brachygluta abdominalis (Aube) newly recorded in Canada (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) with notes on other beach-drift beetles. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 108 (4): 761 - 764." type="journal article" year="2006">Majka and Ogden (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. Its distribution in Atlantic 
<collectingCountry box="[674,760,1011,1037]" name="Canada" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">Canada</collectingCountry>
and Maine is shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka and Ogden" firstAuthor="Majka" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" pagination="761 - 764" refId="ref17421" refString="Majka CG, Ogden J (2006) Brachygluta abdominalis (Aube) newly recorded in Canada (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) with notes on other beach-drift beetles. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 108 (4): 761 - 764." type="journal article" year="2006">Majka and Ogden (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. The species is found in leaf litter in salt marshes and sand dune areas and in beach drift at the upper margin of the intertidal zone (
<bibRefCitation author="Majka and Ogden" firstAuthor="Majka" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" pagination="761 - 764" refId="ref17421" refString="Majka CG, Ogden J (2006) Brachygluta abdominalis (Aube) newly recorded in Canada (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) with notes on other beach-drift beetles. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 108 (4): 761 - 764." type="journal article" year="2006">Majka and Ogden 2006</bibRefCitation>
). Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.G. Thomson" authorityYear="1859" box="[340,468,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[340,468,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">Brachygluta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are specialist predators of mites (
<bibRefCitation author="Hammond" box="[842,1040,1117,1143]" firstAuthor="Hammond" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" pagination="247 - 302" refId="ref16451" refString="Hammond PM (2000) Coastal Staphylinidae (rove beetles) in the British Isles, with special reference to saltmarshes. In: Sherwood BR, Gardiner BG, Harris T (Eds) British Saltmarshes: Joint symposium on British Saltmarshes organized between the Linnean Society of London, the Royal Society for the Protection of Birds, and English Nature. Cardigan, London, 247 - 302." type="book chapter" year="2000">Hammond 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
